The paper discusses the use of adversarial learning as a defensive tool to obfuscate and mask private information, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) fields. The paper also involves the training of classifiers and investigating their resolve against adversarial learning methods, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY) categories.
